        "passed": false,
        "feedback": "The generated object is a flat 2D disk with zero volume (bounding box Y-length is 0.0), which is clearly visible in the renders. This happened because `revolve(360, (0, 0, 0), (0, 0, 1))` interprets the axis points in the LOCAL coordinates of the 'XZ' Workplane. In the 'XZ' plane, the local Z-axis is normal to the plane. Revolving around the local Z-axis simply spins the 2D profile within its own plane, resulting in a flat 2D shape. To revolve around the global Z-axis, you must revolve around the 'XZ' plane's local Y-axis. Change the revolve command to `profile.revolve(360, (0, 0), (0, 1))`. Additionally, it is best practice to start your profile explicitly using `.moveTo(0, 0)` before chaining `.lineTo()` commands to ensure the starting point is defined before closing the wire.",
